description: ‚ÄúAs my pop continued to struggle with various health issues, I was imagining what my life would be like without him and how terribly I‚Äôd miss him. While the song is incredibly personal, I think anyone can relate to the idea of having a profound loss in their life. I never intended ‚ÄòDistance‚Äô to be the very first piece of music people would hear from me, but I also thought my father would be here to celebrate its release. This is for him. description: Video shows how to make French toast. French toast ‚Äì one of the most popular homemade dishes in French cuisine. In France, they call French toast ‚Äì ‚ÄúPain Perdu‚Äù (it means lost bread). This recipe explains how to make French toast (SWEET) as a dessert course for breakfast. Using this original French toast recipe, you will make a tasty dessert in 8-10 min for breakfast. The main ingredients of recipe are bread, egg and milk. All other ingredients of this recipe for staffing and garnishing you can change on your own taste. Enjoy this easy and quick 1 min video recipe how to make original French toast from HowToMin!Sweet French toast Recipe:INGREDIENTS:‚Ä¢ 4 thick slices of baguette‚Ä¢ 1 large egg ‚Ä¢ 50ml (1.7 fl. oz.) milk or cream ‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp. sugar ‚Ä¢ 1/4 tsp cinnamon ‚Ä¢ pinch of salt ‚Ä¢ splash of vanilla extract ‚Ä¢ butter for cooking‚Ä¢ Greek yogurt, jam and Blueberries for garnishIMPORTANT:You can use fresh or stale bread for this recipe of the French toast. HOW TO MAKE FRENCH TOAST:Stir the egg with milk - 50ml (1.7 fl. oz.)Add sugar, salt, cinnamon and a drop of vanilla extract  Stir wellCut 4 thick (about 2 inch) slices of baguette (or any other stale bread)Pour the mix in a plateArrange the bread slices and leave them to soak for 2 minFlip the slices and leave them to soakHeat the pan and melt butterPlace the bread and sear 2 min from each sideSpread a cooking dish with butterCook in oven about 5-6 min 320ÀöF (160ÀöC)Garnish with Greek yogurt, blueberries and mint leavesEnjoy your tasty French toast!WEBSITE: https://howtomin.com FOLLOW US ON:INSTAGRAM: https://www.instagram.com/howtomin_com FACEBOOK: https://www.facebook.com/howtomin/ TWITTER: https://twitter.com/howtomin_com  TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@howtomin

title: Fixing The UNFIXABLE: Squishy Makeovers from The Hopeless Bin
tags: squishy makeover|painting on things|tiktok painting|things to paint on|fun painting projects|how to fix squishies
description: Hey guys! Today I am doing a video that was honestly DEMANDED by some people in my comment sections recently üòÇ Many of you really wanted to see my attempt to Fix The Unfixable, sooooo, here I go. This special episode of squishy makeovers will be me attempting to fix and redecorate squishies from the WORST or worst. These extremely damaged squishies come from my hopeless bin and I was honestly not sure if they would ever make it out!Also, I am aware that this whole spamming of my comment setions kind of started a war between those who were doing it and those who thought it was really annoying üòÇ I appreciate those of you who didn't want me to be pressured into doing a video I didn't want to do! Don't worry, I'm happy to give it a try. And I appreciate getting video requests from you guys.DON'T FORGET ABOUT THE COUSIN DERP PLUSH!https://moriahelizabethmerch.com/AND The new Christmas apparel design is now available here:https://moriah-elizabeth.teespring.com/listing/special-holiday-collection?product=345_________FAQs__________1. CAN I SEND YOU SQUISHIES?So many generous people have sent me their unwanted squishies so I actually have a lot to work on already, BUT if you desperately want to, you can request my mailing address in the email ALLLL the way at down in the description (sorry for the traveling), make sure to read the disclaimer down there as well.2. ARE SQUISHIES RETURNED TO THE SENDERS AFTER THE MAKEOVER?No. These squishies  are sent as donations to the series because they were damaged, and no longer wanted. Everyone has been informed in advance that squishies would not be returned. It would be waaay too complicated/expensive and massively time consuming to keep track of everyone and return each squishy. I'm just one person! 3. WHAT PAINT DO YOU USE?I use fabric paint. Fabric paint is meant to stretch, so it is perfect for squishing! Any brand will work fine, but I mainly use Tulip. You can find it at Michaels, Hobby Lobby, A.C. Moore, Walmart, Joann Fabrics, and Online.5. WILL FABRIC PAINT CRACK?The matte fabric paint is more likely to crack after lots of squishing. Slick fabric paints never crack. But there are benefits to both. I usually mix the two paints together to get the best of both worlds.___________WELCOME TO MY CHANNEL__________Hey! my name is Moriah (pronounced muh-rye-yuh üòÇ ) and this is my channel....obviously. I'm 25 and like doing anything creative...and being snarky.....just a lil. I make a lot of decorating, painting and general art videos here. I'm obsessed with editing and adding lil bits to my videos, so if that's not your thing....oof you may hate this haha. I paint on squishies, thrift store finds, and other random things I pick up. I also love to draw, but don't expect anything too skilled, I'm not the best at that haha. You will also find occasional crafting/testing crafting kits on my channel which are always a hot mess. And even some baking (REALLY bad at that, but it's fun to try LOL). CURRENT SERIES:Squishy Makeovers: Fixing and decorating used squishies sent from my viewersThrift Store Makeovers: Fixing and decorating stuff I find at thrift stores/yard salesBake With ME: Recreating squishies I've decorated in real lifeCreate This Book: Drawing in the prompt book that I wrote (available to purchase and follow along)Squishy Unboxing: Opening used squishy packages sent from viewersCraft Kit Testing: pretty self explanatory. testing craft kits.___UPLOAD SCHEDULE___Every Friday at 4:00pm ET: Alternating Squishy Makeovers, Thrift Makeovers, Craft Kit Reviews, Create This Book, Mail Openings and Miscellaneous crafts and DIYs____PURCHASE ME PRODUCTS____CREATE THIS BOOK:https://amzn.to/2vUerfICREATE THIS BOOK 2:https://amzn.to/2Nx2G9fME Custom Merchandise:https://moriahelizabethmerch.com/ME Pin & Sticker Shop:https://me-merch.myshopify.comME Printed Apparel and Accessories:https://moriah-elizabeth.teespring.com/____ME SOCIALS____INSTAGRAM: https://www.instagram.com/moriahelizabethofficial/TIKTOK:https://www.tiktok.com/@me.moriah.elizabethVISIT ME WEBSITE:https://www.moriahelizabeth.com/____CONTACT ME____EMAIL PICTURES OF YOUR ART (Create This Book or Fan art only please):Artwork@Moriah.videoFOR BUSINESS INQUIRIES/OPPORTUNITIES ONLY:moriah@nightmedia.co_____MAIL ME_____For sending squishies, Letters, or general fan mail, please contact: FANMAIL@MORIAH.VIDEO to request my P.O. box address (must be 13+ to send mail)ATTENTION: Unfortunately I can only respond to a small amount of people each week. title: THIS CHANGES EVERYTHING | Building Our Home in the Woods

description: We've Escaped to the Wilderness & We're Building our Home at a Cabin in the Woods. This week we make some BIG changes üòä It's Jackery's 8th Anniversary! To celebrate they are offering 15% off all of their products from November 16th-18th. Check it out here: https://www.jackery.com/pages/jackery-8th-anniversary‚ñ∫ SUBSCRIBE for a new video every single Sunday http://bit.ly/2DDSUgu‚ñ∫ The vlog continues on Instagram https://instagram.com/eamonandbecHere it is friends: the new adventure we've been dreaming and saving for since we first met 8 years ago. We've always envisioned moving into the woods by the lake and building our dream tiny cabin as a home base for us to come back to in between our international travels. We cannot wait to have a place to call our own!! After 4 weeks up here we are really settling into the slow pace of life and the peace and quiet. And this week we tackle two projects that CHANGE EVERYTHING for us up here!!! üå≤  Looking forward to all of the home renovations and cabin improvements we'll be tackling this winter!Catch up on our cabin in the woods videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZJRuafNYdPweo6S8x6hvPZowmbLrkFM7Eamon & Bec Products‚Ü† handmade chai blends https://chaiwalachai.com/ ‚Üû‚Ü† cookbook https://www.eamonandbec.com/weekday-whip-ups ‚Üû‚Ü† professional photo filters https://www.eamonandbec.com/presets ‚Üû‚Ü† van build guide https://www.eamonandbec.com/vanbuild ‚ÜûHow Did We Get Here?Abandoning our Van in Africa  https://bit.ly/2Kff0HTAfter an incredible 3 years of living, working, and traveling in our self converted Sprinter Van we made the very tough decision to abandon it in Africa to take a rescue flight back to Canada.  As it has for all of us this global pandemic has flipped our world upside down.  When our Prime Minister announced that he was sending repatriation flights over to Africa to pick up Canadians who were stuck (due to border closures) we consulted with friends and family closest to us and realized that in this time of crisis we should be back in our home country. Halting our dream of driving around the world was a hard pill to swallow which is why we knew we needed a big project to keep our mind + body busy while social distancing back here in Toronto. Enter building an off-grid tiny house on wheels!! But after nearly 6 months, we realized that our dreams of continuing van life across North America in our new van build were not a current reality with the state of the world. So, we've found ourselves pursuing something we've dreamed of since we first got together 8 years ago... a cabin in the woods üòä Tour the renovations we've done to our self converted sprinter van:VAN TOUR after 2 years living in our TINY HOUSE on wheels http://bit.ly/newvantourWhat's in Our Camera Bag? https://www.eamonandbec.com/blogWho are we?We're Eamon and Bec, a Toronto-based couple who live full-time in our self converted Sprinter Van!! SUBSCRIBE for wanderlust travel, behind the scenes of what it's really like to live in a van, and videos all about the yummy vegan food we make + eat! VAN LIFE COUPLE. Our goal here is to inspire you to chase after your own dreams however big (or small... tiny homes anyone?) they may be! We hope to create a community of like-minded, positive individuals who will grow to love and support one another on their own journeys.
